00:02:42,398 --> 00:02:44,180
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"The Winner Takes it All"</font>

61
00:02:44,305 --> 00:02:46,305
<font color=#ffff00>Sync corrections</font>  by  <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

62
00:02:47,407 --> 00:02:49,681
Oh, I'm sorry
I missed your scan.

63
00:02:49,779 --> 00:02:52,634
Oh, please.
I went in. I came out.

64
00:02:52,759 --> 00:02:54,524
Same as the first
million times.

65
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,196
Well, I could have
been there for you.

66
00:02:56,282 --> 00:02:58,173
You had a good excuse.

67
00:02:58,595 --> 00:03:00,771
There's my girl!

68
00:03:00,856 --> 00:03:03,975
There's my girl!

69
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:05,543
Let me get her for you.
Relax.

70
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:07,634
Do you want to go
to Grandma?

71
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,481
Say, "Hi, Grandma."
"Hi, Grandma."

72
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:12,483
Hey!
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

73
00:03:12,568 --> 00:03:14,485
Did Koracick re-check
the CT angio?

74
00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:16,487
Yes,
and please stop.

75
00:03:16,572 --> 00:03:18,604
I appreciate both of you
wanting to be a part of this,

76
00:03:18,689 --> 00:03:20,892
but I have
a crackerjack neuro team.

77
00:03:20,977 --> 00:03:23,306
I need you to be my husband
and my son today.

78
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,595
And
we need you to be our patient.

79
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:28,971
Hmm, Thomas, you're getting
ready to cut open my spine.

80
00:03:29,056 --> 00:03:30,835
I will be
whatever I want.

81
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:32,637
Oh. Music to my ears.

82
00:03:32,722 --> 00:03:35,033
Now, we will go in
posteriorly

83
00:03:35,119 --> 00:03:36,126
with our stealth system

84
00:03:36,235 --> 00:03:38,345
and our newly pilfered
ORBEYE scope.

85
00:03:38,431 --> 00:03:39,462
Hmm.

86
00:03:39,548 --> 00:03:41,900
The plan is to go in
and remove it en bloc.

87
00:03:41,986 --> 00:03:43,548
And you really think
that posteriorly

88
00:03:43,634 --> 00:03:44,517
is the way to go?

89
00:03:44,603 --> 00:03:47,556
Oh, it is fun to have so many
surgeons in one family.

90
00:03:47,642 --> 00:03:48,885
Remind me, Avery...
When did you become

91
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:50,673
double board certified in neuro?

92
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:52,243
That's really how you talk
to your patient's family?

93
00:03:52,328 --> 00:03:53,704
It is, actually.

94
00:03:56,197 --> 00:03:57,862
We need to
go in posteriorly

95
00:03:57,947 --> 00:03:59,931
to avoid the carotid
and the jugular,

96
00:04:00,017 --> 00:04:02,462
and to avoid having to weave
through the brachial plexus.

97
00:04:02,548 --> 00:04:04,935
Look, I know how hard
it is to be on the bench,

98
00:04:05,021 --> 00:04:06,771
but we are the A-Team.
And we don't lose.

99
00:04:06,856 --> 00:04:09,774
Just ask Shepherd's tumor.
Oh, wait, you can't.

100
00:04:09,859 --> 00:04:11,809
Because I removed it.
Flawlessly.

101
00:04:12,017 --> 00:04:14,278
Okay,
any last questions?

102
00:04:14,363 --> 00:04:16,881
Um... it looks like
you've got this.

103
00:04:16,966 --> 00:04:18,001
We do.

104
00:04:18,121 --> 00:04:19,665
Mm-hmm.

105
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:22,720
I'm good.

106
00:04:22,805 --> 00:04:25,017
But, you know, I-I um...

107
00:04:25,502 --> 00:04:29,821
I think I'd like to
just take a little walk

108
00:04:30,156 --> 00:04:31,773
before we get started.

109
00:04:32,111 --> 00:04:34,392
- I'd be happy to...
- Oh, no, honey.

110
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,619
I want to go alone.

111
00:04:37,052 --> 00:04:38,642
Okay, then,
but no guarantees

112
00:04:38,728 --> 00:04:40,033
I won't watch you
walk away.

113
00:04:40,119 --> 00:04:41,478
You always do.

114
00:05:17,622 --> 00:05:18,876
Hi. I'm...

115
00:05:18,961 --> 00:05:20,161
Meredith?

116
00:05:20,482 --> 00:05:21,544
Yeah.

117
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:23,458
I'm sorry.
You look...

118
00:05:23,544 --> 00:05:25,114
just like
your picture.

119
00:05:25,599 --> 00:05:27,286
You're the surgeon,
right?

120
00:05:27,372 --> 00:05:28,622
Yeah.

121
00:05:31,528 --> 00:05:33,294
Uh, do you
want to come in?

122
00:05:34,435 --> 00:05:35,793
That's a loaded
question.

123
00:05:44,966 --> 00:05:46,419
I'm not sure
if he's awake.

124
00:05:46,505 --> 00:05:48,204
He sleeps more and more
these days

125
00:05:48,290 --> 00:05:49,607
as you can imagine.

126
00:05:49,872 --> 00:05:51,809
Uh, can I get
you something?

127
00:05:51,894 --> 00:05:53,849
Water? Gin, maybe?

128
00:05:56,215 --> 00:05:57,411
All right.

129
00:05:58,825 --> 00:06:01,778
Thatcher?
You have a visitor.

130
00:06:10,803 --> 00:06:12,553
Meredith!

131
00:06:14,788 --> 00:06:16,000
Hi...

132
00:06:18,094 --> 00:06:19,420
Hi.

133
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:24,654
He's not on any pain meds.
Clean and sober.

134
00:06:24,835 --> 00:06:25,999
His wishes.

135
00:06:26,085 --> 00:06:27,710
So, just the oxygen,
if he needs it.

136
00:06:27,795 --> 00:06:29,170
But you know
how that works.

137
00:06:29,256 --> 00:06:30,483
I do.

138
00:06:30,998 --> 00:06:32,348
Well,
I'll leave you to it.

139
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:33,957
My cellphone number
is on the fridge.

140
00:06:34,043 --> 00:06:35,877
If you need anything,
give me a call.

141
00:06:48,436 --> 00:06:51,193
I probably
can't stay very long.

142
00:06:51,279 --> 00:06:52,990
I just...

143
00:06:55,627 --> 00:06:58,378
There's so much to say,
I-I...

144
00:06:58,580 --> 00:07:00,531
I don't know what to say.

145
00:07:02,037 --> 00:07:04,209
I didn't come here
to say anything

146
00:07:04,497 --> 00:07:06,506
or to hear you
say anything to me, so...

147
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:08,233
we can just sit,
if that's okay.

148
00:07:08,443 --> 00:07:09,498
Okay.

149
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,296
Mom.

150
00:07:45,388 --> 00:07:47,091
I was looking for you.

151
00:07:51,381 --> 00:07:53,521
You know I give Amelia
and Koracick a hard time,

152
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:55,162
but... they're the best.

153
00:07:55,248 --> 00:07:57,732
I was thinking about
my first surgery.

154
00:07:57,885 --> 00:08:01,060
The very first time
I held a scalpel in my hand.

155
00:08:01,282 --> 00:08:04,653
It was a simple lipoma,
but I was terrified.

156
00:08:04,778 --> 00:08:06,021
Hmm.

157
00:08:06,207 --> 00:08:08,891
I expected to feel
so powerful, invincible.

158
00:08:08,977 --> 00:08:10,411
But the second
that scrub nurse

159
00:08:10,564 --> 00:08:12,732
put that 10 blade
in my hand,

160
00:08:12,965 --> 00:08:14,182
I went ice cold.

161
00:08:14,290 --> 00:08:16,574
Okay, so then
what did you do?

162
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:20,130
Diana Ross.
"Ain't No Mountain High Enough."

163
00:08:20,216 --> 00:08:22,258
The first time
I heard that song,

164
00:08:22,343 --> 00:08:25,428
it just filled me with joy
and such calm...

165
00:08:25,513 --> 00:08:26,724
so I just sang it

166
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:29,021
over and over and over
in my head, in that O.R.,

167
00:08:29,107 --> 00:08:33,135
until that same sense of calm
and joy washed over me.

168
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,704
And it's been
my secret weapon

169
00:08:34,789 --> 00:08:36,706
for everything
that's ever scared me...

170
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:38,007
My first surgery.

171
00:08:38,092 --> 00:08:40,443
Labor with you,
it was on an endless loop.

172
00:08:41,810 --> 00:08:45,435
Every PET scan,
every MRI.

173
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:49,615
I remember you singing that song
in the kitchen

174
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:51,184
when I was doing
my homework.

175
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:53,220
You told me it was old people music.

176
00:08:53,306 --> 00:08:54,823
You wanted Michael Jackson.

177
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:56,892
I love me some Michael.
Ooh.

178
00:08:56,978 --> 00:08:59,196
I had to pry that
red leather jacket off of you

179
00:08:59,282 --> 00:09:00,380
to get you to go to bed
at night.

180
00:09:00,465 --> 00:09:02,816
Ah, that's true.

181
00:09:03,050 --> 00:09:04,302
Oh.

182
00:09:04,504 --> 00:09:06,286
I guess I used to do
the same thing.

183
00:09:06,372 --> 00:09:09,290
My first surgery,
I sang a song in my head.

184
00:09:09,376 --> 00:09:11,860
- I mean, it calmed me, you know?
- I know.

185
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,508
I watched you.

186
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,910
My first...
How did you watch?

187
00:09:15,996 --> 00:09:18,514
Child, please.
I am Catherine Fox.

188
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:19,715
Do you think
there's a world

189
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,350
where I wouldn't
sneak into the gallery

190
00:09:21,435 --> 00:09:22,888
of my baby's
first surgery?

191
00:09:23,097 --> 00:09:25,341
Oh, you were a sight
to see...

192
00:09:25,473 --> 00:09:26,896
Mm.

193
00:09:27,068 --> 00:09:30,086
I bet Harriet does
the same thing someday.

194
00:09:30,226 --> 00:09:33,021
Well, I'll be sneaking up
into the gallery with you, then.

195
00:09:34,348 --> 00:09:35,614
Deal.

196
00:09:36,869 --> 00:09:38,661
That's a deal.

197
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:42,607
Now, can we please get you
to your room?

198
00:09:42,857 --> 00:09:44,427
Not yet.

199
00:09:45,227 --> 00:09:48,276
- Mom...
- I left the foundation in your name,

200
00:09:48,362 --> 00:09:50,079
just in case
anything happens to me.

201
00:09:50,164 --> 00:09:52,192
Cecilia runs
the day-to-day operations,

202
00:09:52,278 --> 00:09:53,683
Charlie keeps
the books humming,

203
00:09:53,768 --> 00:09:56,247
but they'll need a leader,
a North Star.

204
00:09:56,771 --> 00:09:59,005
And in the event that I'm left
totally paralyzed...

205
00:09:59,091 --> 00:10:00,289
Mom, even if
you can't operate,

206
00:10:00,374 --> 00:10:01,557
you're still gonna run
the foundation, okay?

207
00:10:01,642 --> 00:10:03,599
You'll teach.
You're Catherine Fox.

208
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:04,981
What are you gonna do?

209
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,829
You're gonna be all up in my
business and everybody else's.

210
00:10:06,914 --> 00:10:08,459
We both know you're gonna
find a way to do that.

211
00:10:08,544 --> 00:10:10,408
Keep this.
Turn the page.

212
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,817
I've already...
Turn the page.

213
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,205
You planned
your own party?

214
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:17,552
Mom.

215
00:10:17,638 --> 00:10:20,376
If I get out of this alive,
the fun we're gonna have...

216
00:10:20,461 --> 00:10:22,745
And don't you even think about
scrimping on those egg rolls.

217
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,099
You know
they're my favorite.

218
00:10:24,371 --> 00:10:27,856
You really
planned everything.

219
00:10:28,035 --> 00:10:29,825
I always do.

220
00:10:30,696 --> 00:10:32,271
All right, then.

221
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:34,599
Shall we?

222
00:10:41,994 --> 00:10:44,599
Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe.

223
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:47,803
Phillip put these everywhere
for me.

224
00:10:48,235 --> 00:10:50,946
He said it's supposed to
be soothing.

225
00:10:51,032 --> 00:10:52,172
Truth be told,

226
00:10:52,258 --> 00:10:53,672
it just makes me
miss it more.

227
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:56,907
A few years back,
a student told me about

228
00:10:57,079 --> 00:11:00,415
a semester he took abroad
building schools.

229
00:11:01,149 --> 00:11:05,235
Lexie was gone,
and I thought I could either

230
00:11:05,726 --> 00:11:07,508
drown my grief
in a bottle of Scotch

231
00:11:07,594 --> 00:11:09,625
or do something.
So I did something.

232
00:11:13,582 --> 00:11:14,688
In Zimbabwe.

233
00:11:14,774 --> 00:11:18,711
The sunsets, Meredith...
and the quiet.

234
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:21,969
The people that I met,
they have this passion

235
00:11:22,055 --> 00:11:26,743
for... life, loving,
learning...

236
00:11:30,493 --> 00:11:32,180
And then you got sick.

237
00:11:32,348 --> 00:11:34,431
I thought
I'd just come home,

238
00:11:34,517 --> 00:11:36,317
do whatever treatment
I needed to do,

239
00:11:36,403 --> 00:11:39,602
and then go back, but...
It was good. Coming home.

240
00:11:39,719 --> 00:11:44,399
It gave me a chance to...
It was the right thing to do.

241
00:11:48,115 --> 00:11:49,915
You went and got
a whole new life.

242
00:11:50,117 --> 00:11:51,850
I did.

243
00:11:53,969 --> 00:11:55,094
I'm glad for you.

244
00:11:55,180 --> 00:11:57,806
I'm glad you saw sunsets
and built schools

245
00:11:57,892 --> 00:12:00,352
for people who needed them
and you stayed sober.

246
00:12:00,540 --> 00:12:02,149
You went and got
a whole new life.

247
00:12:02,258 --> 00:12:04,719
Halfway across the world
this time.

248
00:12:06,586 --> 00:12:07,875
But you didn't
give a damn

249
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:09,660
about the people
you left behind.

250
00:12:13,977 --> 00:12:15,056
Say it again.

251
00:12:15,219 --> 00:12:18,125
We make an incision posteriorly
from C3 to T4,

252
00:12:18,211 --> 00:12:19,261
and then use
